ZCZC GE79
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
A HIGH 1039 SHOULD START THE PERIOD DOMINANT OVER THE UK AND IRELAND
LYING CENTRED OVER SEERN ENGLAND. AT THIS TIME LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS WILL
BE HELD AT SOME DISTANCE TO THE NW. TOWARDS MIDWEEK A NEW DEEP LOW IS EXP
TO MOV EWARDS ACROSS ICELAND REACHING NORWEGIAN BASIN AND THEN SCANDINAVIA
THROUGH WEDNESDAY AS THE HIGH DECLINES. A SECOND LOW MAY FOLLOW ON THE HEELS
OF THE FIRST LOW LATER WEDNESDAY PERHAPS CROSSING THE FAEROES AND NERN ISLES
EWARDS LATER. THESE FEATURES MAY THEN AMALGAMATE AND FILL IN THE VICINITY
OF SCANDINAVIA TO END THE PERIOD FORMING A LARGE AND COMPLEX LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE HERE WITH THE MAIN HIGH HAVING RETROGRESSED INTO THE MID-ATLANTIC.
A SWATHE OF GALES MAY DEVELOP ACROSS FAR NERN CULLERCOATS TUESDAY PROBABLY
EASING FOR A TIME MIDWEEK BEFORE A FURTHER RISK OF GALES BRIEFLY SEV AFFECTS
FAR NERN AND LATER NERN CULLERCOATS MORE GENERALLY INTO THURSDAY MOV BODILY
SEWARDS AND EASING
